DICOM

NIDM-E BIDS DICOM SIO OBO ONLI

DICOM: Types and relations

Classes | Datatype Properties | Object Properties

Classes

dicom:'Specialization'

dicom:'Specialization': Specialization is the replacement of the Type, value range and/or description of an Attribute in a general Module of an IOD, by its Type, value range and/or description defined in a modality-specific Module of an IOD. Note: The same Attribute may be present in multiple Modules in the same IOD but not specified to be specialized.

dicom:'Specialization' is a prov:Activity.

Type: owl:Class

Curation Status: obo:IAO_0000428

dicom:'Data Set'

dicom:'Data Set': Exchanged information consisting of a structured set of Attributes. The value of each Attribute in a Data Set is expressed as a Data Element.

dicom:'Data Set' is a prov:Entity.

Type: owl:Class

Curation Status: obo:IAO_0000428

dicom:'Data Stream'

dicom:'Data Stream': The result of encoding a Data Set using the DICOM encoding scheme (Data Element Numbers and representations as specified by the Data Dictionary).

dicom:'Data Stream' is a prov:Entity.

Type: owl:Class

Curation Status: obo:IAO_0000428

dicom:'Information Object'

dicom:'Information Object': An abstraction of a real information entity (e.g., CT Image, Structured Report, etc.) that is acted upon by one or more DICOM Commands. Note: This term is primarily used in PS3.1, with a few references in PS3.3. It is an informal term corresponding to a formal term that is introduced in PS3.3. In all other parts of the DICOM Standard this formal term is known as an Information Object Definition.

dicom:'Information Object' is a prov:Entity.

Type: owl:Class

Same as: sio:SIO_000015

Curation Status: obo:IAO_0000428

dicom:'Functional Group'

dicom:'Functional Group': A set of logically related Attributes that are likely to vary together. May be used in Multi-frame IODs to describe parameters that change on a per frame basis.

dicom:'Functional Group' is a prov:Entity.

Type: owl:Class

Curation Status: obo:IAO_0000428

dicom:'Module'

dicom:'Module': A set of Attributes within an Information Entity or Normalized IOD that are logically related to each other.

dicom:'Module' is a prov:Entity.

Type: owl:Class

Curation Status: obo:IAO_0000428

dicom:'Data Set'

dicom:'Data Set': Exchanged information consisting of a structured set of Attribute values directly or indirectly related to Information Objects. The value of each Attribute in a Data Set is expressed as a Data Element. A collection of Data Elements ordered by increasing Data Element Tag number that is an encoding of the values of Attributes of a real world object.

dicom:'Data Set' is a prov:Entity.

Type: owl:Class

Curation Status: obo:IAO_0000428

dicom:'Nested Data Set'

dicom:'Nested Data Set': A Data Set contained within a Data Element of another Data Set. Data Sets can be nested recursively. Only Data Elements with Value Representation Sequence of Items may, themselves, contain Data Sets.

dicom:'Nested Data Set' is a prov:Entity.

Type: owl:Class

Curation Status: obo:IAO_0000428

dicom:'Sequence of Items'

dicom:'Sequence of Items': A Value Representation for Data Elements that contain a sequence of Data Sets. Sequence of Items allows for Nested Data Sets. (The Value Representation is denoted SQ.).

dicom:'Sequence of Items' is a prov:Entity.

Type: owl:Class

Curation Status: obo:IAO_0000428

dicom:'Value Field'

dicom:'Value Field': The field within a Data Element that contains the Value(s) of that Data Element.

dicom:'Value Field' is a prov:Entity.

Type: owl:Class

Curation Status: obo:IAO_0000428

dicom:'Value Representation Field'

dicom:'Value Representation Field': The field where the Value Representation of a Data Element is stored in the encoding of a Data Element structure with explicit VR.

dicom:'Value Representation Field' is a prov:Entity.

Type: owl:Class

Curation Status: obo:IAO_0000428

dicom:'Application Profile'

dicom:'Application Profile': A Media Storage Application Profile defines a selection of choices at the various layers of the DICOM Media Storage Model that are applicable to a specific need or context in which the media interchange is intended to be performed.

dicom:'Application Profile' is a prov:Entity.

Type: owl:Class

Curation Status: obo:IAO_0000428

dicom:'File Meta Information'

dicom:'File Meta Information': The File Meta Information includes identifying information on the encapsulated Data Set. It is a mandatory header at the beginning of every DICOM File.

dicom:'File Meta Information' is a prov:Entity.

Type: owl:Class

Curation Status: obo:IAO_0000428

dicom:'File-set'

dicom:'File-set': A File-set is a collection of DICOM Files (and possibly non-DICOM Files) that share a common naming space within which File IDs are unique.

dicom:'File-set' is a prov:Entity and has the following child: dicom:'Secure File-set'.

Type: owl:Class

Curation Status: obo:IAO_0000428

dicom:'Media Storage Services'

dicom:'Media Storage Services': DICOM Media Storage Services define a set of operations with media that facilitate storage to and retrieval from the media of DICOM SOP Instances.

dicom:'Media Storage Services' is a prov:Entity.

Type: owl:Class

Curation Status: obo:IAO_0000428

dicom:'Secure File-set'

dicom:'Secure File-set': A File-set in which all DICOM Files are Secure DICOM Files.

dicom:'Secure File-set' is a dicom:'File-set'.

Type: owl:Class

Curation Status: obo:IAO_0000428

dicom:'Secure Media Storage Application Profile'

dicom:'Secure Media Storage Application Profile': A DICOM Media Storage Application Profile that requires a Secure File-set.

dicom:'Secure Media Storage Application Profile' is a prov:Entity.

Type: owl:Class

Curation Status: obo:IAO_0000428

dicom:'File-set Creator'

dicom:'File-set Creator': An Application Entity that creates the DICOMDIR File (see Section 8.6) and zero or more DICOM Files.

dicom:'File-set Creator' is a prov:Agent.

Type: owl:Class

Curation Status: obo:IAO_0000428

dicom:'File-set Reader'

dicom:'File-set Reader': An Application Entity that accesses one or more files in a File-set.

dicom:'File-set Reader' is a prov:Agent.

Type: owl:Class

Curation Status: obo:IAO_0000428

dicom:'File-set Updater'

dicom:'File-set Updater': An Application Entity that accesses Files, creates additional Files, or deletes existing Files in a File-set. A File-set Updater makes the appropriate alterations to the DICOMDIR file reflecting the additions or deletions.

dicom:'File-set Updater' is a prov:Agent.

Type: owl:Class

Curation Status: obo:IAO_0000428

dicom:'Attribute'

dicom:'Attribute': A property of an Information Object. An Attribute has a name and a value that are independent of any encoding scheme.

dicom:'Attribute' is a prov:Entity.

Type: owl:Class

Same as: sio:SIO_000614

Curation Status: obo:IAO_0000428

dicom:'Command'

dicom:'Command': A request to operate on information across a network.

dicom:'Command' is a sio:SIO_000091.

Type: owl:Class

Curation Status: obo:IAO_0000428

dicom:'Command Element'

dicom:'Command Element': An encoding of a parameter of a command that conveys this parameters value.

dicom:'Command Element' is a sio:SIO_000612.

Type: owl:Class

Curation Status: obo:IAO_0000428

dicom:'Command Stream'

dicom:'Command Stream': The result of encoding a set of DICOM Command Elements using the DICOM encoding scheme.

dicom:'Command Stream' is a sio:SIO_000612.

Type: owl:Class

Curation Status: obo:IAO_0000428

dicom:'Conformance Statement'

dicom:'Conformance Statement': A formal statement that describes a specific product implementation that uses the DICOM Standard. It specifies the Service Classes, Information Objects, and Communication Protocols supported by the implementation.

dicom:'Conformance Statement' is a sio:SIO_000136.

Type: owl:Class

Curation Status: obo:IAO_0000428

dicom:'Data Dictionary'

dicom:'Data Dictionary': A registry of DICOM Data Elements that assigns a unique tag, a name, value characteristics, and semantics to each Data Element. Data Element A unit of information as defined by a single entry in the data dictionary.

dicom:'Data Dictionary' is a sio:SIO_000090.

Type: owl:Class

Curation Status: obo:IAO_0000428

dicom:'Information Object Class'

dicom:'Information Object Class': A formal description of an Information Object, which includes a description of its purpose and the Attributes it possesses. It does not include values for these attributes. Note This term is only used in PS3.1. It is an informal term corresponding to a formal term that is introduced in PS3.4. This formal term is known as a Service-Object Pair Class or more commonly as a SOP Class.

dicom:'Information Object Class' is a sio:SIO_000136.

Type: owl:Class

Curation Status: obo:IAO_0000428

dicom:'Information Object Instance'

dicom:'Information Object Instance': A representation of an occurrence of an real-world entity, which includes values for the Attributes of the Information Object Class to which the entity belongs. Note This term is only used in PS3.1. It is an informal term corresponding to a formal term that is introduced in PS3.4. This formal term is known as a Service-Object Pair Instance or more commonly as a SOP Instance.

dicom:'Information Object Instance' is a sio:SIO_000396.

Type: owl:Class

Curation Status: obo:IAO_0000428

dicom:'Message'

dicom:'Message': A data unit of the Message Exchange Protocol exchanged between two cooperating DICOM Applications. A Message is composed of a Command Stream followed by an optional Data Stream.

dicom:'Message' is a sio:SIO_000602.

Type: owl:Class

Curation Status: obo:IAO_0000428

dicom:'Service Class'

dicom:'Service Class': A structured description of a service that is supported by cooperating DICOM Applications using specific DICOM Commands acting on a specific class of Information Object.

dicom:'Service Class' is a sio:SIO_000136.

Type: owl:Class

Curation Status: obo:IAO_0000428

dicom:'Acquisition Context'

dicom:'Acquisition Context': A description of the conditions present during data acquisition.

dicom:'Acquisition Context' is a sio:SIO_000136.

Type: owl:Class

Curation Status: obo:IAO_0000428

dicom:'Acquisition Protocol Element'

dicom:'Acquisition Protocol Element': A sequential component of an acquisition protocol, that contains the SCANNING PARAMETERS necessary to perform a single SCAN. In the case of CT this would correspond to tube voltage, tube current, rotation time, spatial location, etc. and an Acquisition Protocol Element also corresponds to an XR-25 PROTOCOL ELEMENT.

dicom:'Acquisition Protocol Element' is a dicom:'Protocol Element'.

Type: owl:Class

Curation Status: obo:IAO_0000428

dicom:'Attribute tag'

dicom:'Attribute tag': A unique identifier for an Attribute of an Information Object composed of an ordered pair of numbers (a Group Number followed by an Element number). Cine run A set of temporally related frames acquired at constant or variable frame rates. This term incorporates the general class of serialography. Note: A Cine run is typically encoded as a multi-frame image.

dicom:'Attribute tag' is a dicom:'Tag'.

Type: owl:Class

Curation Status: obo:IAO_0000428

dicom:'Code Sequence Attribute'

dicom:'Code Sequence Attribute': Attribute that (usually) includes the string 'Code Sequence' in the Attribute Name and has a VR of SQ (Sequence of Items). Its purpose is to encode concepts using code values and optional text meanings from coding schemes. Section 8.1 through Section 8.8 specify the Attributes of which the Sequence Items (Attribute Sets) of Code Sequence Attributes are constructed.

dicom:'Code Sequence Attribute' is a sio:SIO_000614.

Type: owl:Class

Curation Status: obo:IAO_0000428

dicom:'Composite IOD'

dicom:'Composite IOD': An Information Object Definition that represents parts of several entities in the DICOM Application Model. Such an IOD includes Attributes that are not inherent in the Real-World Object that the IOD represents but rather are inherent in related Real-World Objects. Derived image an image in which the pixel data was constructed from pixel data of one or more other images (source images).

dicom:'Composite IOD' is a sio:SIO_000136.

Type: owl:Class

Curation Status: obo:IAO_0000428

dicom:'DICOM application model'

dicom:'DICOM application model': An Entity-Relationship diagram used to model the relationships between Real-World Objects that are within the area of interest of the DICOM Standard.

dicom:'DICOM application model' is a sio:SIO_000510.

Type: owl:Class

Curation Status: obo:IAO_0000428

dicom:'DICOM Information Model'

dicom:'DICOM Information Model': An Entity-Relationship diagram that is used to model the relationships between the Information Object Definitions representing classes of Real-World Objects defined by the DICOM Application Model.

dicom:'DICOM Information Model' is a sio:SIO_000510.

Type: owl:Class

Curation Status: obo:IAO_0000428

dicom:'Information entity'

dicom:'Information entity': That portion of information defined by a Composite IOD that is related to one specific class of Real-World Object. There is a one-to-one correspondence between Information Entities and entities in the DICOM Application Model. Information object definition (IOD) a data abstraction of a class of similar Real-World Objects that defines the nature and Attributes relevant to the class of Real-World Objects represented.

dicom:'Information entity' is a sio:SIO_000015.

Type: owl:Class

Curation Status: obo:IAO_0000428

dicom:'Multi-frame Image'

dicom:'Multi-frame Image': Image that contains multiple two-dimensional pixel planes.

dicom:'Multi-frame Image' is a dct:Image.

Type: owl:Class

Curation Status: obo:IAO_0000428

dicom:'Normalized IOD'

dicom:'Normalized IOD': An Information Object Definition (IOD) that represents a single entity in the DICOM Application Model. Such an IOD includes Attributes that are only inherent in the Real-World Object that the IOD represents.

dicom:'Normalized IOD' is a sio:SIO_000136.

Type: owl:Class

Curation Status: obo:IAO_0000428

dicom:'Protocol Element'

dicom:'Protocol Element': A sequential component of a protocol, consisting of all the parameters necessary to perform that component of the protocol.

dicom:'Protocol Element' is a sio:SIO_000091 and has the following children: dicom:'Acquisition Protocol Element', dicom:'Reconstruction Protocol Element', dicom:'Storage Protocol Element'.

Type: owl:Class

Curation Status: obo:IAO_0000428

dicom:'Reconstruction Protocol Element'

dicom:'Reconstruction Protocol Element':

dicom:'Reconstruction Protocol Element' is a dicom:'Protocol Element'.

Type: owl:Class

Curation Status: obo:IAO_0000428

dicom:'Storage Protocol Element'

dicom:'Storage Protocol Element': A sequential component of a storage protocol, such as sending a series of images to a PACS or an archive or a processing workstation.

dicom:'Storage Protocol Element' is a dicom:'Protocol Element'.

Type: owl:Class

Curation Status: obo:IAO_0000428

dicom:'Unique Device Identifier'

dicom:'Unique Device Identifier': An alphanumeric identifier issued by the unique device identification system established by the FDA to label and identify devices through distribution and use. See http://www.fda.gov/udi.

dicom:'Unique Device Identifier' is a dicom:'Unique Identifier'.

Type: owl:Class

Curation Status: obo:IAO_0000428

dicom:'Basic Offset Table'

dicom:'Basic Offset Table':

dicom:'Basic Offset Table' is a sio:SIO_000612.

Type: owl:Class

Curation Status: obo:IAO_0000428

dicom:'Big Endian'

dicom:'Big Endian': A form of byte ordering where multiple byte binary values are encoded with the most significant byte encoded first, and the remaining bytes encoded in decreasing order of significance.

dicom:'Big Endian' is a sio:SIO_000612.

Type: owl:Class

Curation Status: obo:IAO_0000428

dicom:'Character Repertoire'

dicom:'Character Repertoire': A finite set of different characters that is considered to be complete for a given purpose and is specified independently of their encoding (also referred to as a character set).

dicom:'Character Repertoire' is a sio:SIO_000612.

Type: owl:Class

Curation Status: obo:IAO_0000428

dicom:'Code String:'

dicom:'Code String:': A string of characters identifying a controlled concept, including Defined Terms and Enumerated Values when represented as character strings. The scope of the controlled concept is limited to the attribute for which the string provides the value; i.e., the attribute defines the allowed set of values for the Code String, and a particular string may have different meanings in different attributes. A Code String is formally an arbitrary code representing a semantic concept; however, English language words (using the constrained character set of the CS Value Representation) are often used as codes for the semantics of those words.

dicom:'Code String:' is a sio:SIO_000651.

Type: owl:Class

Curation Status: obo:IAO_0000428

dicom:'Data Element'

dicom:'Data Element': A unit of information as defined by a single entry in the data dictionary. An encoded Information Object Definition (IOD) Attribute that is composed of, at a minimum, three fields: a Data Element Tag, a Value Length, and a Value Field. For some specific Transfer Syntaxes, a Data Element also contains a VR Field where the Value Representation of that Data Element is specified explicitly.

dicom:'Data Element' is a sio:SIO_000651 and has the following children: dicom:'Item Delimitation Data Element', dicom:'Private Data Element', dicom:'Retired Data Element', dicom:'Standard Data Element'.

Type: owl:Class

Curation Status: obo:IAO_0000428

dicom:'Data Element Tag'

dicom:'Data Element Tag': A unique identifier for a Data Element composed of an ordered pair of numbers (a Group Number followed by an Element Number).

dicom:'Data Element Tag' is a dicom:'Tag'.

Type: owl:Class

Curation Status: obo:IAO_0000428

dicom:'Data Element Type'

dicom:'Data Element Type': Used to specify whether an Attribute of an Information Object Definition or an Attribute of a SOP Class Definition is mandatory, mandatory only under certain conditions, or optional. This translates to whether a Data Element of a Data Set is mandatory, mandatory only under certain conditions, or optional.

dicom:'Data Element Type' is a sio:SIO_000179.

Type: owl:Class

Curation Status: obo:IAO_0000428

dicom:'Defined Term'

dicom:'Defined Term': The Value of a Data Element is a Defined Term when the Value of the element may be one of an explicitly specified set of standard values, and these values may be extended by implementers.

dicom:'Defined Term' is a sio:SIO_000651.

Type: owl:Class

Curation Status: obo:IAO_0000428

dicom:'Element Number'

dicom:'Element Number': The second number in the ordered pair of numbers that makes up a Data Element Tag.

dicom:'Element Number' is a sio:SIO_000115.

Type: owl:Class

Curation Status: obo:IAO_0000428

dicom:'Enumerated Value'

dicom:'Enumerated Value': The Value of a Data Element is an Enumerated Value when the value of the element must be one of an explicitly specified set of standard values, and these values shall not be extended by implementers.

dicom:'Enumerated Value' is a sio:SIO_000366.

Type: owl:Class

Curation Status: obo:IAO_0000428

dicom:'Group Number'

dicom:'Group Number': The first number in the ordered pair of numbers that makes up a Data Element Tag.

dicom:'Group Number' is a sio:SIO_000115.

Type: owl:Class

Curation Status: obo:IAO_0000428

dicom:'Item'

dicom:'Item': A component of the Value of a Data Element that is of Value Representation Sequence of Items.

dicom:'Item' is a sio:SIO_000651 and has the following child: dicom:'Sequence Delimitation Item'.

Type: owl:Class

Curation Status: obo:IAO_0000428

dicom:'Item Delimitation Data Element'

dicom:'Item Delimitation Data Element': Used to mark the end of an Item of Undefined Length in a Sequence of Items. This is the last Data Element in an Item of Undefined Length.

dicom:'Item Delimitation Data Element' is a dicom:'Data Element'.

Type: owl:Class

Curation Status: obo:IAO_0000428

dicom:'Little Endian'

dicom:'Little Endian': A form of byte ordering where multiple byte binary values are encoded with the least significant byte encoded first; and the remaining bytes encoded in increasing order of significance.

dicom:'Little Endian' is a sio:SIO_000612.

Type: owl:Class

Curation Status: obo:IAO_0000428

dicom:'Pixel Cell'

dicom:'Pixel Cell': The container for a single Pixel Sample Value that may include unused bits. The size of a Pixel Cell shall be specified by the Bits Allocated (0028, 0100) Data Element.

dicom:'Pixel Cell' is a sio:SIO_000015.

Type: owl:Class

Curation Status: obo:IAO_0000428

dicom:'Pixel Data'

dicom:'Pixel Data': Graphical data (e.g., images) of variable pixel-depth encoded in the Pixel Data, Float Pixel Data or Double Float Pixel Data Element.

dicom:'Pixel Data' is a dct:Image.

Type: owl:Class

Curation Status: obo:IAO_0000428

dicom:'Pixel Sample Value'

dicom:'Pixel Sample Value': A value associated with an individual pixel. An individual pixel consists of one or more Pixel Sample Values (e.g., color images).

dicom:'Pixel Sample Value' is a sio:SIO_000070.

Type: owl:Class

Curation Status: obo:IAO_0000428

dicom:'Private Data Element'

dicom:'Private Data Element': Additional Data Element, defined by an implementer, to communicate information that is not contained in Standard Data Elements. Private Data elements have odd Group Numbers.

dicom:'Private Data Element' is a dicom:'Data Element'.

Type: owl:Class

Curation Status: obo:IAO_0000428

dicom:'Repeating Group'

dicom:'Repeating Group': Standard Data Elements within a particular range of Group Numbers where elements that have identical Element Numbers have the same meaning within each Group (and the same VR, VM, and Data Element Type). Repeating Groups shall only exist for Curves and Overlay Planes (Group Numbers (50xx,eeee) and (60xx,eeee), respectively) and are a remnant of versions of this standard prior to V3.0.

dicom:'Repeating Group' is a sio:SIO_000115.

Type: owl:Class

Curation Status: obo:IAO_0000428

dicom:'Retired Data Element'

dicom:'Retired Data Element': A Data Element that is unsupported beginning with Version 3.0 of this standard. Implementations may continue to support Retired Data Elements for the purpose of backward compatibility with versions prior to V3.0, but this is not a requirement of this version of the standard.

dicom:'Retired Data Element' is a dicom:'Data Element'.

Type: owl:Class

Curation Status: obo:IAO_0000428

dicom:'Sequence Delimitation Item'

dicom:'Sequence Delimitation Item': Item used to mark the end of a Sequence of Items of Undefined Length. This Item is the last Item in a Sequence of Items of Undefined Length.

dicom:'Sequence Delimitation Item' is a dicom:'Item'.

Type: owl:Class

Curation Status: obo:IAO_0000428

dicom:'Standard Data Element'

dicom:'Standard Data Element': A Data Element defined in the DICOM Standard, and therefore listed in the DICOM Data Element Dictionary in PS3.6.

dicom:'Standard Data Element' is a dicom:'Data Element'.

Type: owl:Class

Curation Status: obo:IAO_0000428

dicom:'Transfer Syntax'

dicom:'Transfer Syntax': A set of encoding rules that allow Application Entities to unambiguously negotiate the encoding techniques (e.g., Data Element structure, byte ordering, compression) they are able to support, thereby allowing these Application Entities to communicate. (This is for both Standard and Private).

dicom:'Transfer Syntax' is a sio:SIO_000651.

Type: owl:Class

Curation Status: obo:IAO_0000428

dicom:'Undefined Length'

dicom:'Undefined Length': The ability to specify an unknown length for a Data Element Value (of Value Representation SQ, UN, OW, or OB) or Item. Data Elements and Items of Undefined Length are delimited with Sequence Delimitation Items and Item Delimiter Data Elements, respectively.

dicom:'Undefined Length' is a sio:SIO_000614.

Type: owl:Class

Curation Status: obo:IAO_0000428

dicom:'Unique Identifier'

dicom:'Unique Identifier': A string of characters that uniquely identifies a wide variety of items; guaranteeing uniqueness across multiple countries, sites, vendors and equipment. (The acronym is UID).

dicom:'Unique Identifier' is a sio:SIO_000115 and has the following children: dicom:'Tag', dicom:'Unique Device Identifier'.

Type: owl:Class

Curation Status: obo:IAO_0000428

dicom:'Value'

dicom:'Value': A component of a Value Field. A Value Field may consist of one or more of these components.

dicom:'Value' is a sio:SIO_000015.

Type: owl:Class

Curation Status: obo:IAO_0000428

dicom:'Value Length'

dicom:'Value Length': The field within a Data Element that contains the length of the Value Field of the Data Element.

dicom:'Value Length' is a sio:SIO_000366.

Type: owl:Class

Curation Status: obo:IAO_0000428

dicom:'Value Multiplicity'

dicom:'Value Multiplicity': Specifies the number of Values contained in the Value Field of a Data Element. (VM).

dicom:'Value Multiplicity' is a sio:SIO_000366.

Type: owl:Class

Curation Status: obo:IAO_0000428

dicom:'Value Representation'

dicom:'Value Representation': Specifies the data type and format of the Value(s) contained in the Value Field of a Data Element. (VR).

dicom:'Value Representation' is a sio:SIO_000179.

Type: owl:Class

Curation Status: obo:IAO_0000428

dicom:'Tag'

dicom:'Tag': A unique identifier for an element of information composed of an ordered pair of numbers (a Group Number followed by an Element Number), which is used to identify Attributes and corresponding Data Elements.

dicom:'Tag' is a dicom:'Unique Identifier' and has the following children: dicom:'Attribute tag', dicom:'Data Element Tag'.

Type: owl:Class

Curation Status: obo:IAO_0000428

dicom:'DICOM File Service'

dicom:'DICOM File Service': The DICOM File Service specifies a minimum abstract view of files to be provided by the Media Format Layer. Constraining access to the content of files by the Application Entities through such a DICOM File Service boundary ensures Media Format and Physical Media independence.

dicom:'DICOM File Service' is a sio:SIO_000090.

Type: owl:Class

Curation Status: obo:IAO_0000428

dicom:'DICOM File'

dicom:'DICOM File': A DICOM File is a File with a content formatted according to the requirements of this Part of the DICOM Standard. In particular such files shall contain, the File Meta Information and a properly formatted Data Set.

dicom:'DICOM File' is a dicom:'File' and has the following child: dicom:'DICOMDIR File'.

Type: owl:Class

Curation Status: obo:IAO_0000428

dicom:'DICOMDIR File'

dicom:'DICOMDIR File': A unique and mandatory DICOM File within a File-set that contains the Media Storage Directory SOP Class. This File is given a single component File ID, DICOMDIR.

dicom:'DICOMDIR File' is a dicom:'DICOM File'.

Type: owl:Class

Curation Status: obo:IAO_0000428

dicom:'File'

dicom:'File': A File is an ordered string of zero or more bytes, where the first byte is at the beginning of the file and the last byte at the end of the File. Files are identified by a unique File ID and may by written, read and/or deleted.

dicom:'File' is a sio:SIO_000602 and has the following children: dicom:'DICOM File', dicom:'Secure DICOM File'.

Type: owl:Class

Same as: sio:SIO_000396

Curation Status: obo:IAO_0000428

dicom:'File ID'

dicom:'File ID': Files are identified by a File ID that is unique within the context of the File-set they belong to. A set of ordered File ID Components (up to a maximum of eight) forms a File ID.

dicom:'File ID' is a sio:SIO_000115.

Datatype Properties

dicom:'File-set ID'

dicom:'File-set ID': User or implementation specific Identifier (up to 16 characters). The File-set ID is intended to be a short human readable label to easily (but not necessarily uniquely) identify a specific File-set to facilitate operator manipulation of the physical media on which the File-set is stored. Assignment of Value and semantics are environment specific.

dicom:'File-set ID' is a nidm:DICOMTag.

Type: owl:DatatypeProperty

Curation Status: obo:IAO_0000428

dicom:'File-set Descriptor File ID'

dicom:'File-set Descriptor File ID': ID of a File (in the same File-set) used for user comments related to the File-set (e.g., a README file). The Specific Character set used may be specified in the Specific Character Set of the File-set Descriptor File (0004,1142). This File is not DICOM formatted (no Preamble, nor DICM Prefix and Meta Information).

dicom:'File-set Descriptor File ID' is a nidm:DICOMTag.

Type: owl:DatatypeProperty

Curation Status: obo:IAO_0000428

dicom:'Specific Character Set of File-set Descriptor File' is a nidm:DICOMTag.

Type: owl:DatatypeProperty

Curation Status: obo:IAO_0000428

dicom:'Offset of the First Directory Record of the Root Directory Entity'

dicom:'Offset of the First Directory Record of the Root Directory Entity': Offset of the first byte (of the Item Data Element) of the first Directory Record of the Root Directory Entity. This Offset is a number of bytes starting with the first byte of the File Meta Information. When the Root Directory Entity contains no Directory Record, this offset shall be set to 00000000H. This offset includes the File Preamble and the DICM Prefix.

dicom:'Offset of the First Directory Record of the Root Directory Entity' is a nidm:DICOMTag.

Type: owl:DatatypeProperty

Curation Status: obo:IAO_0000428

dicom:'Offset of the Last Directory Record of the Root Directory Entity'

dicom:'Offset of the Last Directory Record of the Root Directory Entity': Offset of the first byte (of the Item Data Element) of the last Directory Record of the Root Directory Entity. This Offset is a number of bytes starting with the first byte of the File Meta Information. When the Root Directory Entity contains no Directory Record, this offset shall be set to 00000000H. This offset includes the File Preamble and the DICM Prefix.

dicom:'Offset of the Last Directory Record of the Root Directory Entity' is a nidm:DICOMTag.

Type: owl:DatatypeProperty

Curation Status: obo:IAO_0000428

dicom:'File-set Consistency Flag': Enumerated Values: 0000H no known inconsistencies The value FFFFH shall never be present. Formerly, this Attribute was intended to signal that the directory was in an inconsistent state with a value of FFFFH. This usage has been retired.

dicom:'File-set Consistency Flag' is a nidm:DICOMTag.

A zero length Value indicates that no Directory Records are contained in the Root Directory Entity.

dicom:'Directory Record Sequence' is a nidm:DICOMTag.

Type: owl:DatatypeProperty

Curation Status: obo:IAO_0000428

dicom:'Offset of the Next Directory Record'

dicom:'Offset of the Next Directory Record': Offset of the first byte (of the Item Data Element) of the next Directory Record of the same Directory Entity. This Offset is an unsigned integer representing a number of bytes starting with the first byte of the File Meta-information. A zero offset shall be used to mean that there is no other Directory Record in this Directory Entity. This Offset may be used to keep an inactive Record (0004,1410) chained with the next Directory Record of the same Directory Entity. This offset includes the File Preamble and the DICM Prefix.

dicom:'Offset of the Next Directory Record' is a nidm:DICOMTag.

Private blocks are identified by their Private Creator Data Element value, rather than their numeric block number, since instances may be modified and numeric block numbers reassigned but the Private Creator Data Element value, which is required to be unique within a Group of Private Data Elements, will be preserved.

Curation Status: obo:IAO_0000428

dicom:'Nonidentifying Private Elements'

dicom:'Nonidentifying Private Elements': List of Private Data Elements in block that do not contain identifying information (are safe from identity leakage). Elements are identified by the lowest 8-bits of the attribute tag (i.e., with a value from 0000H to 00FFH) within the block, stored as an unsigned short integer. Multiple values shall be in increasing order and a given value shall be listed at most once.

dicom:'Acquisition Motion'

dicom:'Acquisition Motion': Motion of scan progression. Defined Terms: SINGLE Scan progresses in a single pass from Acquisition Start Location to Acquisition End Location. SHUTTLE Scan progresses from Acquisition Start Location to Acquisition End Location, then reverses direction and scans back to Acquisition Start Location. NOMOTION All slices are acquired simultaneously. NOTIMPORTANT Acan either direction is acceptable. The value of NOT_IMPORTANT is not permitted in the Performed Procedure Protocol IOD.

dicom:'Acquisition Motion' is a nidm:DICOMTag.

dicom:'Acquisition Start Location Sequence'

dicom:'Acquisition Start Location Sequence': Anatomically oriented transverse location where this acquisition starts. This represents the nominal start location. Due to overscan, tissue may be irradiated beyond this location. In a Defined Procedure Protocol, this represents the intended start location. The operator may or may not select a location that exactly matches this anatomical location. In a Performed Procedure Protocol, this value may have been copied from the Defined Procedure Protocol and may not represent the exact anatomical location selected by the operator. Only a single item is permitted in the sequence.

dicom:'Acquisition Start Location Sequence' is a nidm:DICOMTag.

dicom:'Visual Acuity Modifiers'

dicom:'Visual Acuity Modifiers': The first value is a positive or negative integer numeric value such as +1, +2, +3, 0, -1, -2, or -3 used to indicate that the patient missed letters on the line referenced, or saw additional letters on the next smaller line. The second value is a positive or negative integer numeric value such as +1, +2, +3, 0, -1, -2, or -3, which in combination with the first value indicates that the patient both saw additional letters on the next smaller line and missed letters on the line referenced. When the modifier values are zero, the values are not typically displayed to the user. .

dicom:'Visual Acuity Modifiers' is a nidm:DICOMTag.

Curation Status: obo:IAO_0000428

dicom:'Decimal Visual Acuity'

dicom:'Decimal Visual Acuity': A patients visual acuity specified in decimal. The value is derived from two values in a fraction where the numerator of the fraction is the nominal distance to the chart that the patient is reading. The denominator represents the line of smallest optotypes of which the patient can see more than half. Typical examples: reference standard is 1, severe vision loss is 0.1.

dicom:'Decimal Visual Acuity' is a nidm:DICOMTag.

Type: owl:DatatypeProperty

Curation Status: obo:IAO_0000428

dicom:'Vertices of the Outline of Pupil'

dicom:'Vertices of the Outline of Pupil': A set of row/column vertices that outline the perimeter of the pupil. Two or more pairs of values follow and are the row and column coordinates of the other vertices that outline the perimeter of the pupil. For a two dimensional curve: X1, Y1, X2, Y2, etc. The first (X) dimension corresponds to the image column (horizontal offset), and the second (Y) dimension corresponds to the image row (vertical offset). This is a Polyline and the points are to be interpreted as an n-tuple list of end points between which straight lines are to be drawn.

dicom:'Corneal I-S Value': Quantifies the inferior-superior dioptric asymmetry along the vertical meridian to discriminate Keratoconus, measured in diopters. See Rabinowitz YS and McDonnell PJ. 'Computer-assisted corneal topography in keratoconus. Refract Corneal Surg. 1989 Nov-Dec;5(6):400-8'.

dicom:'Corneal Point Location' is a nidm:DICOMTag.

Curation Status: obo:IAO_0000428

dicom:'Corneal Point Estimated' is a nidm:DICOMTag.

Type: owl:DatatypeProperty

Curation Status: obo:IAO_0000428

dicom:'Axial Power'

dicom:'Axial Power': Conveys corneal shape characteristics, in diopters. It is determined from the curvature, r in mm, of the equivalent sphere with the same slope at a given point on the surface. Axial power = Km/r, where Km is the Keratometric Index.

dicom:'Axial Power' is a nidm:DICOMTag.

Type: owl:DatatypeProperty

Curation Status: obo:IAO_0000428

dicom:'Tangential Power'

dicom:'Tangential Power': Determined from the curvature (2nd derivative = d2y/dx2) of a point on the cornea, in diopters; also called Instantaneous Power. Emphasizes irregular astigmatism (large variations in higher order aberrations).

dicom:'Tangential Power' is a nidm:DICOMTag.

Type: owl:DatatypeProperty

Curation Status: obo:IAO_0000428

dicom:'Refractive Power'

dicom:'Refractive Power': Conveys the optical refraction properties of the cornea, in diopters. It is determined from ray tracing using Snells Law to calculate the true refractive power. It is used to evaluate ocular optics.

dicom:'Refractive Power' is a nidm:DICOMTag.

Type: owl:DatatypeProperty

Curation Status: obo:IAO_0000428

dicom:'Relative Elevation'

dicom:'Relative Elevation': Relative elevation, in micrometers, is calculated from the corneal surface distance from a reference surface (i.e., a sphere or ellipsoid) that intersects the corneal vertex. This value is determined from z - zref. Where z is conveyed in Attribute Corneal Point Location (0046,0247) and zref is the elevation of the reference surface.

dicom:'Relative Elevation' is a nidm:DICOMTag.

Type: owl:DatatypeProperty

Curation Status: obo:IAO_0000428

dicom:'Corneal Wavefront'

dicom:'Corneal Wavefront': Corneal wavefront, in micrometers, is calculated from the elevation data by fitting with the Zernike Series expansion. This permits measurement of both low and higher order aberrations and provides the total amount of distortion of the Corneal Wavefront with a Root Mean Square (RMS) value.

dicom:'Corneal Wavefront' is a nidm:DICOMTag.

Type: owl:DatatypeProperty

Curation Status: obo:IAO_0000428

dicom:'Abstract Prior Value'

dicom:'Abstract Prior Value': Identifies a prior image set in abstract terms. Exactly two integer values, indicating the range of prior studies to include. Each value shall be greater than zero, where 1 indicates the most recent prior and higher values indicate successively older priors. The special value -1 shall indicate the oldest prior. The value pair n,n indicates the nth prior. The value pair -1/-1 indicates the oldest prior. The value pair m/n indicates the mth through nth priors, where m is the more recent prior. The value pair 1/-1 indicates all priors. The value pair m/-1 indicates the mth prior and all priors older than m. Required if Image Set Selector Category (0072,0034) is ABSTRACT_PRIOR and Abstract Prior Code Sequence (0072,003E) is not present.

dicom:'Abstract Prior Value' is a nidm:DICOMTag.

dicom:'Overlay Origin'

dicom:'Overlay Origin': Location of first overlay point with respect to pixels in the image, given as row/column. The upper left pixel of the image has the coordinate 1/1. Column values greater than 1 indicate the overlay plane origin is to the right of the image origin. Row values greater than 1 indicate the overlay plane origin is below the image origin. Values less than 1 indicate the overlay plane origin is above or to the left of the image origin. Values of 0/0 indicate that the overlay pixels start 1 row above and one column to the left of the image pixels.

dicom:'Overlay Origin' is a nidm:DICOMTag.

dicom:'Overlay Bits Allocated': Number of Bits Allocated in the Overlay. The value of this Attribute shall be 1. Formerly the standard described embedding the overlay data in the Image Pixel Data (7FE0,0010), in which case the value of this Attribute was required to be the same as Bits Allocated (0028,0100). This usage has been retired.

dicom:'Overlay Bits Allocated' is a nidm:DICOMTag.

Type: owl:DatatypeProperty

Curation Status: obo:IAO_0000428

dicom:'Overlay Bit Position'

dicom:'Overlay Bit Position': The value of this Attribute shall be 0. Formerly the standard described embedding the overlay data in the Image Pixel Data (7FE0,0010), in which case the value of this Attribute specified the bit in which the overlay was stored. This usage has been retired.

dicom:'Overlay Bit Position' is a nidm:DICOMTag.

Type: owl:DatatypeProperty

Curation Status: obo:IAO_0000428

dicom:'Overlay Activation Layer'

dicom:'Overlay Activation Layer': The layer (defined in Graphic Layer (0070,0002) of the in which the Overlay described in group 60xx shall be displayed. If no layer is specified (zero length) then the overlay shall not be displayed.

dicom:'Overlay Activation Layer' is a nidm:DICOMTag.

Type: owl:DatatypeProperty

Curation Status: obo:IAO_0000428

dicom:'Overlay Label'

dicom:'Overlay Label': A user defined text string that may be used to label or name this overlay.

dicom:'Overlay Label' is a nidm:DICOMTag.

Type: owl:DatatypeProperty

Curation Status: obo:IAO_0000428

dicom:'Overlay Data'

dicom:'Overlay Data': Overlay pixel data. The order of pixels encoded for each overlay is left to right, top to bottom, i.e., the upper left pixel is encoded first followed by the remainder of the first row, followed by the first pixel of the 2nd row, then the remainder of the 2nd row and so on. Overlay data shall be contained in this Attribute.

dicom:'Overlay Data' is a nidm:DICOMTag.

Type: owl:DatatypeProperty

Curation Status: obo:IAO_0000428

dicom:'Float Pixel Data'

dicom:'Float Pixel Data': A data stream of the pixel samples that comprise the Image. The order of pixels encoded for each image plane is left to right, top to bottom, i.e., the upper left pixel (labeled 1,1) is encoded first followed by the remainder of row 1, followed by the first pixel of row 2 (labeled 2,1) then the remainder of row 2 and so on.

dicom:'Float Pixel Data' is a nidm:DICOMTag.

Type: owl:DatatypeProperty

Curation Status: obo:IAO_0000428

dicom:'Double Float Pixel Data'

dicom:'Double Float Pixel Data': A data stream of the pixel samples that comprise the Image. The order of pixels encoded for each image plane is left to right, top to bottom, i.e., the upper left pixel (labeled 1,1) is encoded first followed by the remainder of row 1, followed by the first pixel of row 2 (labeled 2,1) then the remainder of row 2 and so on.

dicom:'Double Float Pixel Data' is a nidm:DICOMTag.

Type: owl:DatatypeProperty

Curation Status: obo:IAO_0000428

dicom:'Pixel Data'

dicom:'Pixel Data': A data stream of the pixel samples that comprise the Image.

dicom:'Pixel Data' is a nidm:DICOMTag.

Type: owl:DatatypeProperty

Curation Status: obo:IAO_0000428
